    value: 저본에는 없다. 저본의 원목차에 근거하여 보충하였다.
english:
  title: In the Refined Style, Remembering the Past
  author: Lee Je
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I recall those days when we launched the painted dragon boat,
    Where man and bird dissolved together in carefree wandering.
    Gentle winds stirred the white gulls on the rippling waters,
    And peaks along the river piled up like jade snails.
    Beneath the waves swam fish as large as rhinoceroses,
    While masts stretched ten leagues, half hidden by the embankment.
    The Yonggang flows now into Mapo's stream,
    And misty peaks shine blue against the clouds.

    I called for wine, trading gold turtle for spirits,
    Drinking deep from parrot cups in endless succession.
    Tambourines thundered as a hundred vessels were drained,
    Our drunken songs exchanged set even the water demons trembling.

    But I, grown old, now lie like a stabled horse,
    Alone in my humble shell, haunted only by memory.
    How I envy your spirit, soaring like a falcon through heaven,
    Your brush dancing across ten thousand pages, dragons writhing wild.
    I imagine Jungjoong plucking the lute strings,
    Playing phoenix songs beneath the moon-lit lake.
    Munyeon, devoted to letters, still finds joy
    In raising his cup to admire the white grains floating in wine.
    Baekwon dwells by the seashore in solitude,
    Spending long days with qin and crane as companions.

    Could we not gather this fellowship once more,
    Riding our humble donkeys together from place to place?
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'painted dragon boat' (채익주) references the legendary pleasure boats of ancient China, symbolizing carefree youth and artistic fellowship.
  - key: ''
    value: References to figures like Jungjoong, Munyeon, and Baekwon appear to be friends or contemporaries of the poet, each representing different pursuits—music, scholarship, and hermitic contemplation.
  - key: ''
    value: The poem employs classical imagery of animals (dragons, phoenixes, cranes) as metaphors for human aspirations and talents.
